    {
      "id": "p009",
      "index": 9,
      "source": "Apple’s $3 trillion market cap has driven $300B+ in supplier capital expenditure over the past decade. Multiple companies count Apple as 40-75% of their revenue. The invisible hand of Apple’s volume requirements reaches through three supply chain layers to build companies Apple will never directly touch.",
